From opening ceremony to powering Olympics venues, Beijing is striving to fulfill its commitment to hold a green and low-carbon Olympics. There have been many discussions around green Olympics and legacy beyond the Games. Though some Western media questioned China’s reliance on coal outside the Olympics, more voices from the international community are lauding Beijing’s efforts to stage a green Olympics. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Lily Lyu analyzes how Beijing has been realizing a green Olympics.